    genetic content`
    - the part of a waybit's content that properly replicates across genetic links
        - e.g. in forming waybit variants, or in maintaining them by intracast text flow
        ( must be selective about this, as in Votorola difference bridging
    - all differences of declared waybit content exclusive of:
        - no start/end tag
            - as these declare linkage etc.
        - no referents (of links and such) external to the waybit
            - as not actually declared, potentially huge, redundant etc.
        - no uniquely personal lines of text
            ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/copy/doc.task
            - as not of interest to others

