    genetic link`
    < a type of (§) intercast link
    - functions
        - declares a waybit to be a member of a waybit population
        - structures the waybit population by nominal lines of genetic descent
        - indicates approval of ancestral waybit content
            ( Votorola-style transitive vote flow ('delegate cascade') in a recombinant text
            - each genetic link is formally a vote
                - whereby the vote caster formally approves (votes for) the content of the parent
                  and (by transitive vote flow) that of the ancestors
            - here 'vote caster' means every waycaster for whom that link is on way
                ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/way#on_way
                - why? to avoid pushing them into forming *direct* links merely to express approval
                  that is already implied by their use (on way) of the ancestors' descendant
    [ general to all forms
        * referring waybit
            - specified by all forms of genetic link
                - this is a waybit local to the declaring waycast
        * *link* attribute
            < cog:link, namespace data:,wayscript.cog
            ( cf: http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/script/doc.task § source nodes: the *link* attribute
            ( optional in some forms
            - a URL in form
            - function (as part of a genetic link)
                - effective only if the referent is:
                    - a waybit
                    - a member of the same population as the *referring waybit*
                - declares
                    - the referent waybit to be a genetic parent
                    - the *referring waybit* to be its child
            - meaning
                - a nominal relation
                    - does not claim an ontic relation
                        - genetics as *actual* generative text flows and editorial influences
                    - rather declares a nominal relation of *intended* genetics
                        - to serve the practical (e.g. collaborative) purpose of the (§) waybit population
                - a genetic relation
                    - as opposed to a waypath parent-child relation
                    ( cf. http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/script/doc.task § waypath relations § genealogical
    [ particular forms
        § intercast waylink
            ( every intercast waylink is a genetic link
            - function (as a genetic link)
                - locates the *referring waybit* as the resolved waylink source node
                - declares the source node to be:
                    - a member of the population identified by the location of the target node
                        ( viz. the value of the source node's *link* attribute in normal URL form
                        - regardless of what population (if any) the target node itself belongs to
                    - potentially a genetic child of the target node
                        ( see § *link* attribute above
                        - in which case, it is a clonal child
        § *variant* element
    - cycles
        - formally possible in lines of descent (*link* attributes)
            ( exactly as in Votorola
        - meaning of cycles will vary with the particular function of the link under consideration
        - effect will vary with the practical context, and may be blocked in some contexts

