    *variant* element`
    - function
        - declares a (§) genetic link
        - replaces the content of the genetic parent (if declared in the link)
            - wherever in the way definition it occurs
            ( no matter how remote from the waycast, how deep (indirect) the linkage
            - with that of the variant
        - effective iff:
             & the parent (referent of *cog:link*)
                - and/or the content (referent of *href*)
                - is on way
                    ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/way#on_way
                - and so proper to the waycaster
                    ( else it's weird
             & the waycast declares another variant of the same population
    - form
          | <variant [cog:link='PARENT-URL'] [cog:population='POPULATION-ID'] [href='CONTENT-URL']>
          |     [CONTENT]
          |     </variant>
        - genetic link, either or both of:
            ( at least one must be declared
            * *link* attribute
                ( § genetic link § *link* attribute
            * *population* attribute
                < cog:population, namespace data:,wayscript.cog
                - identifier of waybit population of which this variant is a member
                - default value: PARENT-URL
        - content, either of:
            * inline content
                - defines a new waybit
                - declares it to be the *referring waybit*
                    ( § genetic link § referring waybit
            * *href* attribute
                < no namespace
                - an intracast, relative reference in form
                    ( https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986#section-4.2
                    - thus proper to the waycaster
                        ( else it's weird
                - locates the *referring waybit*
                    ( § genetic link § referring waybit
    - placement: on way
        ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/way#on_way
        - if only to make it easily reachable by processors

