    waybit population`
    < a type of intercast network
    - a group of waybits interrelated by nominal lines of descent
    - purpose
        - competitive and collaborative way definition among waycasters
            ( akin to recombinant text in textbender and Votorola
        - efficient editorial search (among waybit variations)
        - formation of way consensus
            ( akin to Votorola poll
    - network link form: genetic link
    - identifier
        - free form string
        - actually, as it happens, a URI
          because it must be referenceable in both forms of genetic link:
            * intercast waylink
                - where it is referenced by the *link* attribute
            * *variant* element
                - where it is referenced by the *population* attribute
            - but here it has no function other than string-based identification
    [ typical practice
        + subsurface variation
            - changing the content of a linked waybit
                - no matter how deep in the waycaster network (indirect) its linkage
                - by making a variant of it
            - the linked waybit
                - is an intercast waylink target node
                - is on way
                - is the waybit you want to change
                - will become the nominal parent of your newly made variant
            - make an empty *variant* element
                - insert it either near to the connecting waylink(s)
                    - or in the root document
                        ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/root#root_document
                    - or anywhere else in your waycast that's on way
            * declaring the parentage
                - add attribute cog:link='PARENT-URL' to reference the chosen parent
                    ( § *variant* element
            * declaring the population
                - skip this if the parent is a member of no waybit population
                    - instead let the population default to PARENT-URL
                - add attribute cog:population='POPULATION-ID' to identify the parent's population
                    - it's declared in the parent waycast
                    - or inferrable from there
                    ( typically a tool will tell you the value
            * declaring the variant content
                - copy the (§) genetic content of the parent
                    - typically a tool does the proper content filtering
                - paste it
                    - either in the *variant* element
                    - or elsewhere, referenced by adding the attribute href='CONTENT-URL'
                - edit the content to change it
        + shallow variation
            - changing the content of a directly linked waybit
            = write this
                - replacing the waylink with a surface variant
                - it ends up formed as a (§) surface variant
        + surface variation
            - pasting the variant content directly in line, no waylinkage
            = write this
                - situation
                    - you already have non-variant waybit
                    - you want to replace its content with variant content
                        - or declare it (as is) to be a variant
                - method
                    - the replacement content is pasted into the waybit (or the waybit is left as is)
                    - a contentless *variant* tag
                        - typically inserted in the same waybit
                            - along with the pasted content
                            - as a waypath child
                        - with an *href* to the waybit
                        - and other attributes as per § subsurface
        + delegation to another waycaster
            - the other waycaster has declared a variant of your waybit, which you like
            - you no longer want to maintain this waybit yourself
            - replace it with an intercast waylink to the variant
              and let the other waycaster maintain it

